## Tradeoff Orientation
- Adoption over feature completeness — tools that people actually use beat impressive tools nobody touches
- Pragmatism over perfection — meet people where they work, integrate into existing platforms
- Execution over strategy decks — "demos over memos"
- Protected thinking time over meeting density — best weeks have uninterrupted deep work blocks
- Human side over tech side — "The tech will be fine. It's the human side that's hard."
- Blurred personal/professional boundary is a feature, not a bug — best work ideas come from personal tinkering

